table_caption: FA values of mean skeleton in HCs, pwMS, and pwMS sub-groups.
table_foot: FA: fractional anisotropy; HCs: healthy controls; MS: multiple sclerosis; MS-no-LUTS: MS patients without lower urinary tract symptoms; MS-OAB: MS patients with OAB; N/A: not applicable; pwMS: patients with MS. Statistically significant difference was found between HCs and pwMS. MS-no-LUTS and MS-OAB were tested using Mann–Whitney U test. *: p < 0.05; **: p < 0.01.
